  <!-- NEWEST CAPABILITIES -->
  <section id="new">
    <p class="eyebrow">New this release</p>
    <h2>It sees your screen, your camera,<br>and your inbox.</h2>
    <p class="muted">The latest build turns SlyOS into a true operator — reading what's in front of you, filing what lands in your inbox, and rendering answers that actually look like answers. Everything flows into one growing memory.</p>
    <div class="demos" style="margin-top:28px">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">Floating brain</div>
        <h3>Read any screen, anywhere</h3>
        <p class="muted">A glassy SlyOS bar floats over every app. Tap the brain and it reads what's on screen, explains it, and remembers it — a chat, a webpage, a form. Swipe it away when you're done.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">Camera &amp; OCR</div>
        <h3>Scan receipts, docs &amp; faces</h3>
        <p class="muted">Point the camera: a receipt logs the expense with line items, any form / ID / invoice auto-files into the right folder, and it recognizes the people you've taught it — front or back lens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">Inbox that files itself</div>
        <h3>Gmail auto-ingest</h3>
        <p class="muted">SlyOS quietly scans incoming mail and PDF attachments for receipts, invoices and forms — turning them into expenses and filed documents in your brain, automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">Rendered, not listed</div>
        <h3>A real calendar view</h3>
        <p class="muted">Ask “what's on my calendar this week” and it draws a clean agenda — grouped by day, times in accent — instead of a plain list. Weather, prices, scores and stock moves render as elegant cards too.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">Never lose the memory</div>
        <h3>Brain backup to Drive</h3>
        <p class="muted">Your whole on-device brain is continuously zipped to your own Google Drive (and Downloads) — surviving uninstalls, wipes and new phones. One-tap restore.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--accent)">No more guessing</div>
        <h3>Validated keys &amp; card settings</h3>
        <p class="muted">Every API key shows a live ✓ Valid / ✗ Invalid dot, all in one place, in a redesigned collapsible-card settings screen — with a clear view of exactly what's in your brain.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

