    <h2>Feed it your history</h2>
    <p class="muted">Optional, but it's what makes the brain actually <em>you</em>. Export your chats from each
      app, then load them in the setup wizard — or anytime under Brain → About (chats) and Now → Reconnect (LinkedIn).</p>
    <div class="imports">
      <div class="imp"><b>WhatsApp</b><p>Open a chat → ⋮ menu → <em>More → Export chat → Without media</em>. Share the <code>.txt</code> to your phone. Repeat per chat.</p></div>
      <div class="imp"><b>LinkedIn</b><p>linkedin.com → <em>Settings → Data privacy → Get a copy of your data</em> → tick <em>Connections</em> &amp; <em>Messages</em>. They email a <code>.zip</code>.</p></div>
      <div class="imp"><b>Instagram</b><p>App or web → <em>Accounts Center → Your information and permissions → Download your information</em> → choose <em>Messages</em>, format <em>JSON</em>.</p></div>
      <div class="imp"><b>Telegram</b><p>Telegram <em>Desktop</em> → <em>Settings → Advanced → Export Telegram data</em> → format <em>Machine-readable JSON</em>.</p></div>
      <div class="imp"><b>Messenger / Facebook</b><p>facebook.com → <em>Settings → Your information → Download your information</em> → <em>Messages</em>, format <em>JSON</em>.</p></div>
      <div class="imp"><b>SMS &amp; the rest</b><p>Incoming texts and any app with a reply box are learned live as you use SlyOS — no export needed.</p></div>
